The paper introduces an algorithmic framework for training mixtures of implicit generative models, which is a topic related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also discusses clustering, which is a topic related to computer vision and neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper proposes a competitive procedure, which is related to game theory and optimization, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the quality of generated samples, which is related to statistical learning and decision making, making cs.SD (Sound) a possible sub-category.
